Solo Career Breakthrough: "Dangerously in Love" (2003)
Beyoncé's debut solo album, "Dangerously in Love" (2003), marked her transition from girl-group member to a global solo star. The album was a massive commercial success, with hits like “Crazy in Love” (featuring Jay-Z) and “Baby Boy.” “Crazy in Love” became one of her signature songs, winning multiple Grammy Awards and solidifying Beyoncé as a pop force to be reckoned with.
